.TH "__vfs_setxattr_noperm" 9 "__vfs_setxattr_noperm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__vfs_setxattr_noperm \- perform setxattr operation without performing permission checks.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __vfs_setxattr_noperm
.BI "(struct user_namespace *mnt_userns "  ","
.BI "struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "const void *value "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mnt_userns" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "dentry" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "name" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "value" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "size" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "flags" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

\fImnt_userns\fP - user namespace of the mount the inode was found from
\fIdentry\fP - object to perform setxattr on
\fIname\fP - xattr name to set
\fIvalue\fP - value to set \fIname\fP to
\fIsize\fP - size of \fIvalue\fP
\fIflags\fP - flags to pass into filesystem operations

returns the result of the internal setxattr or setsecurity operations.

This function requires the caller to lock the inode's i_mutex before it
is executed. It also assumes that the caller will make the appropriate
permission checks.
